{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T08:54:58.019Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Loss Computation — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Loss Computation Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Loss computation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the step in the training loop that measures how far the model's predictions are from the actual values. It mathematically quantifies the discrepancy between predictions (outputs) and true target values (labels) using a loss function, also known as a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "criterion"}, {"type": "text", "text": " or "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "objective function"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The goal of training is to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "minimize this loss value"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — a smaller loss indicates that the model's predictions are closer to the actual targets for the given batch."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Loss Computation Matters in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Different generative models require specialized loss functions:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model Type"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss Function"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Purpose"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "GAN"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Binary Cross-Entropy (BCE)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Discriminator classifies real vs fake"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Diffusion"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mean Squared Error (MSE)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Predict noise to remove from image"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Autoencoder"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MSE / L1 Loss"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reconstruct input image accurately"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Transformer (LLM)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-Entropy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Predict next token probability"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "StyleGAN"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Wasserstein Loss"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Better training stability, no mode collapse"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The loss function:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Measures prediction error"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Provides optimization target"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Guides weight updates"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Loss Computation Works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In the Training Loop Context"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Conceptual implementation of training loop\nfor epoch in range(n_epochs):\n    for batch_idx in range(n_batches):\n        # 1. Get batch\n        X_batch, y_batch = get_batch(batch_idx)\n        \n        # 2. Forward pass\n        y_pred = model(X_batch)  # Predictions [web:80]\n        \n        # 3. Loss computation ← what we're explaining\n        loss = loss_function(y_batch, y_pred)  # [web:80]\n        \n        # 4. Backward pass\n        gradients = tape.gradient(loss, model.weights)  # [web:80]\n        \n        # 5. Optimizer step\n        optimizer.apply_gradients(zip(gradients, model.weights))  # [web:80]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss Computation Formula"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "def compute_loss(y_true, y_pred):\n    # Example: Mean Squared Error\n    return tf.reduce_mean(tf.square(y_true - y_pred))  # [web:80]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The loss is a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "scalar tensor"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (single-element tensor) that summarizes the model's performance on the batch."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Loss Functions in PyTorch"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. Mean Squared Error (MSE Loss)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch.nn as nn\n\ncriterion = nn.MSELoss()  # Instantiate once [web:89]\n\n# During training\noutputs = model(inputs)  # Forward pass [web:89]\nloss = criterion(outputs, labels)  # [web:89]\n\n# Formula: MSE = (1/n) * Σ(y_true - y_pred)² [web:89]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use for"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Regression tasks (predicting continuous values), diffusion models"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. Cross-Entropy Loss (Classification)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()  # [web:89]\n\n# Expects: raw logits (unnormalized) + class indices\noutputs = model(inputs)  # Shape: [batch, num_classes] [web:89]\nlabels = target_classes   # Shape: [batch] (integers) [web:89]\nloss = criterion(outputs, labels)  # [web:89]\n\n# Combines LogSoftmax + NLLoss in one class [web:89]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use for"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Multi-class classification, LLM next-token prediction"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. Binary Cross-Entropy with Logits (BCEWithLogitsLoss)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "criterion = nn.BCEWithLogitsLoss()  # [web:89]\n\n# Expects: raw logits (not probabilities)\noutputs = model(inputs)  # Shape: [batch, 1] [web:89]\nlabels = target_binary    # Shape: [batch] (0 or 1) [web:89]\nloss = criterion(outputs, labels)  # [web:89]\n\n# Combines Sigmoid + BCE for numerical stability [web:89]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use for"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Binary classification, multi-label classification, GAN discriminators"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Loss Functions in TensorFlow/Keras"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. Sparse Categorical Cross-Entropy"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import tensorflow as tf\n\nloss_fn = tf.keras.losses.SparseCategoricalCrossentropy(from_logits=True)  # [web:91]\n\n# Forward pass\npredictions = model(images, training=True)  # [web:91]\n\n# Compute loss\nloss = loss_fn(labels, predictions)  # [web:91]\n\n# from_logits=True: expects raw logits (not probabilities) [web:91]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. Mean Squared Error"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "loss_fn = tf.keras.losses.MeanSquaredError()\n\n# Compute loss\nloss = loss_fn(y_true, y_pred)  # [web:89]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss Computation in Generative AI Models"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "GAN Loss (Binary Cross-Entropy)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch.nn as nn\n\n# Loss function (instantiate once)\ncriterion = nn.BCEWithLogitsLoss()\n\n# Training loop\nfor real_images in dataset:\n    # Forward pass: discriminator\n    real_pred = discriminator(real_images)  # Real images\n    fake_images = generator(noise)\n    fake_pred = discriminator(fake_images)  # Fake images\n    \n    # Loss computation\n    real_loss = criterion(real_pred, real_labels)  # real_labels = 1 [web:89]\n    fake_loss = criterion(fake_pred, fake_labels)  # fake_labels = 0 [web:89]\n    \n    d_loss = (real_loss + fake_loss) / 2  # Average discriminator loss [web:89]\n    \n    # Forward pass: generator\n    fake_images = generator(noise)\n    fake_pred = discriminator(fake_images)\n    \n    # Generator loss (want discriminator to think fakes are real)\n    g_loss = criterion(fake_pred, real_labels)  # [web:89]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Diffusion Model Loss (MSE)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch.nn as nn\n\ncriterion = nn.MSELoss()  # [web:89]\n\n# Training loop\nfor images in dataset:\n    # Add noise\n    t = random_timestep(batch_size)\n    noise = torch.randn_like(images)\n    noisy_images = add_noise(images, noise, t)\n    \n    # Forward pass\n    predicted_noise = diffusion_model(noisy_images, t)\n    \n    # Loss computation\n    loss = criterion(predicted_noise, noise)  # [web:89]\n    \n    # Backward pass\n    loss.backward()\n    optimizer.step()"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Transformer/LLM Loss (Cross-Entropy)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch.nn as nn\n\ncriterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()  # [web:89]\n\n# Training loop\nfor batch in dataset:\n    input_ids = batch['input_ids']\n    labels = batch['labels']  # Next token IDs\n    \n    # Forward pass\n    outputs = transformer(input_ids)  # Shape: [batch, seq_len, vocab_size] [web:89]\n    \n    # Loss computation\n    # Reshape for CrossEntropyLoss: [batch * seq_len, vocab_size]\n    loss = criterion(outputs.view(-1, outputs.size(-1)), labels.view(-1))  # [web:89]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Properties of the Loss Tensor"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "loss = criterion(outputs, labels)  # [web:89]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The resulting "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "loss"}, {"type": "text", "text": " tensor:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Property"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Description"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Scalar"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Single-element tensor (sum/mean of all batch losses)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Connected to graph"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Still linked to computation graph from forward pass"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "requires_grad=True"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Implicitly has gradient tracking enabled"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Starting point for backprop"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Used to compute gradients via "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "loss.backward()"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The loss tensor knows which operations and which model parameters contributed to its final value."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss Computation with Multiple Outputs"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "with tf.GradientTape() as tape:\n    # Main task loss\n    main_loss = compute_main_loss(model, batch)  # [web:80]\n    \n    # Regularization loss\n    reg_loss = compute_regularization(model)  # [web:80]\n    \n    # Total loss\n    total_loss = main_loss + reg_loss  # [web:80]\n\n# Gradients computed for total_loss\ngradients = tape.gradient(total_loss, model.weights)  # [web:80]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss Computation in Custom Training Loops"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "PyTorch Custom Loop"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\nimport torch.nn as nn\nimport torch.optim as optim\n\n# Instantiate loss function once\ncriterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()  # [web:89]\noptimizer = optim.Adam(model.parameters())\n\n# Training loop\nfor epoch in range(epochs):\n    for inputs, labels in dataset:\n        # 1. Zero gradients\n        optimizer.zero_grad()\n        \n        # 2. Forward pass\n        outputs = model(inputs)  # [web:89]\n        \n        # 3. Loss computation\n        loss = criterion(outputs, labels)  # [web:89]\n        \n        # 4. Backward pass\n        loss.backward()  # [web:89]\n        \n        # 5. Optimizer step\n        optimizer.step()\n        \n        # 6. Logging\n        print(f\"Loss: {loss.item()}\")  # Convert to Python float [web:89]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "TensorFlow Custom Loop"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import tensorflow as tf\n\nloss_fn = tf.keras.losses.SparseCategoricalCrossentropy(from_logits=True)  # [web:91]\noptimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam()\n\n# Custom training step\ndef train_step(images, labels):\n    with tf.GradientTape() as tape:\n        # Forward pass\n        predictions = model(images, training=True)  # [web:91]\n        \n        # Loss computation\n        loss = loss_fn(labels, predictions)  # [web:91]\n    \n    # Compute gradients\n    gradients = tape.gradient(loss, model.trainable_variables)  # [web:91]\n    \n    # Update weights\n    optimizer.apply_gradients(zip(gradients, model.trainable_variables))  # [web:91]\n    \n    return loss\n\n# Complete training loop\nEPOCHS = 5\nfor epoch in range(EPOCHS):\n    for images, labels in train_ds:\n        loss = train_step(images, labels)  # [web:91]\n        print(f\"Training loss: {loss.numpy():.4f}\")  # [web:91]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of loss computation as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "getting feedback on a test"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Model takes test"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Forward pass produces predictions"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Teacher grades it"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Loss compares predictions to correct answers"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Score calculated"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Loss is a single number (e.g., 0.85 = bad, 0.05 = good)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Student learns"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Backward pass shows which mistakes to fix"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Student improves"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Optimizer updates weights"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The loss function is the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "scorekeeper"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that tells the model how well it's doing — lower score = better performance."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Loss function"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Measures discrepancy between predictions and true targets"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Goal"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Minimize loss value through training"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Lower loss"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Predictions closer to actual targets"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Scalar tensor"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Loss is a single-element tensor summarizing batch performance"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PyTorch"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Instantiate once outside loop ("}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "TensorFlow"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Define loss function ("}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "loss_fn = tf.keras.losses.SparseCategoricalCrossentropy()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "MSE Loss"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Regression, diffusion models (predict continuous values)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cross-Entropy"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Multi-class classification, LLMs (predict class probabilities)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "BCEWithLogits"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Binary classification, GAN discriminators (real vs fake)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Computation graph"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Loss stays connected to forward pass for gradient computation"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "requires_grad=True"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Loss implicitly has gradient tracking enabled"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Backprop starting point"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "loss.backward()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " computes gradients from loss"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "loss.item()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Convert to Python float for logging"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The loss value serves as the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "starting point for backpropagation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", which adjusts the model's weights to hopefully produce a lower loss on subsequent iterations."}]}]}}